# >>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>><<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<
# >>>> If you want to scan large portion of your parameter space (central/offset) <<<<
# >>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>><<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<
#
# For instance, for mSUGRA+QEWSB, so N=5 parameters
# TanBeta(central) = 13
# TanBeta(offset) = 40

# Fix the proposal width to the expected typical length of the parameter space
# such that the Markov chain can reach both point while sitting in the middle
# ( 40 - 13 ) / 2 = 13.5
# In addition, if the N=5 parameters are fitted together, the width of each parameter has to be scaled by 1/sqrt(N)
# 13.5 / sqrt(5) = 6.0

# The same calcul has to be performed for each parameter
# The minimum should be then spotted with a few tens thousands points

########################################################################################################
########################################################################################################

# >>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>><<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<
# >>>> If you want to scan small portion of your parameter space                  <<<<
# >>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>><<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<
#
# Once the minimum has been roughly spotted, the chain can be adapted to scan finely its contours.

# Add these lines in your input file (for UseMarkovChains = on)

UpdateWidths                    on
UpdateWidthsScale               2

# Then, every 1000 accepted points, the variance of the points distributions is estimated
# and the proposal width is fixed to sqrt(variance) / UpdateWidthsScale

# ATTENTION
# >> If your constraints are weak (no Omega and no g-2), rather use UpdateWidthsScale = 5, 
# >> you can check the evolution of the proposal widths in the output root file of the Markov chain
# >> If you use a very high dimensionnal model (MSSM18...), 1000 points may not be enough, take care


# You can also include correlations by switching on
CorrelationInMarkovChain        on

# ATTENTION
# >> If using correlations does not bring anything, better switching it off than risking a divergence

########################################################################################################
########################################################################################################
